# Model Information

## Waste Classification Model

This project uses the EfficientNet-B0 deep learning architecture for waste image classification.

### Model Details

* Architecture: EfficientNet-B0
* Framework: PyTorch
* Model File: WasteIqEfficient.pth
* Task: Waste Classification

### Performance

The EfficientNet-B0 model was trained on a labeled waste dataset and achieved an accuracy of **[97.16]%** on the test dataset.

### Why EfficientNet-B0?

EfficientNet-B0 was selected because it provides a good balance between accuracy and computational efficiency. It uses compound scaling to optimize network depth, width, and resolution, resulting in strong performance with fewer parameters compared to traditional CNN architectures.

### Note

The trained model file (`WasteIqEfficient.pth`) is not included in this repository because GitHub has file size limitations. The repository contains the complete source code, training pipeline, and model architecture required to reproduce the results.

For access to the trained model weights, please contact the project author.
